result.name: sensory ZERO [ 500 DAYS OF CAFE ]

reviews.text: Nice little cafe & restaurant in the district which offer something different to the community. It offers healthy choices as well as omni pork which is not easy to find in the area. It also provides a variety of choices of coffee and drinks and thus make it a place to meet your friends and clients for a quick catch up. Staff are extremely friendly, good location and quality food.
Nice staff who have interest in their work. The menu can be less confusing.
It's cozy cafe restaurant. I ordered the pasta of the day. The volume is enough for me.  Their big kitchen can be seen from the table and we can enjoy the comfortability. The taste is so-so.

Really nice new cafe. Didn't try the meatless pork but will do next time. A good range of coffees and nice staff.

Update: meatless pork tastes like meat but the ginger latte is soooo ginger! Maybe too ginger?
Good comfort food. Quite busy during lunchtime, but definitely a good place to grab a quick lunch. Would definitely return.
